<test1>
<ptxt>Rapidly reduce the tire pressure for each wheel at least 40 kPa (0.41 kg/cm<sup>2, 5.8 psi) within 30 seconds.</sup>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check the DATA LIST.</ptxt>
<atten3>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>It takes about 1 minutes or more to display the updated tire pressure data.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>When no "TIREPRESS" data has changed, reset the tire pressure to the appropriate specified value and rotate the tire 90 to 270 degrees. Then rapidly release the tire pressure and recheck it.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Record the transmitter ID of which "TIREPRESS" data corresponds to each tire.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten3>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>After confirming that one of "TIREPRESS" data for one tire (ID1 to ID4 or ID5) has changed, repeat this procedure one by one. Identify the transmitter that corresponds to DTC.</ptxt>
</test1>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
